WHAT THIS DOES
──────────────
Converts ANY PDF to Excel with the same accuracy as the "I Love PDF" website:
  • Every character extracted and placed in the correct column
  • Section headers, sub-headers, data rows all styled distinctly
  • Multi-column grid forms (IRS f6765, f4797, f8825…) → proper column layout
  • Table-based PDFs (tax returns) → full table with headers
  • Free-text PDFs (MD Form 202) → positional text placement
  • Line numbers placed in their correct right-hand column
  • Dot leaders (......) absorbed, not written as garbage
  • All values forced to TEXT format — Excel never auto-reformats numbers
  • Zero data loss — sub-row overflow prevents any content being dropped
  • Multiple pages → separate worksheets, each named "Page N"
  • Column widths and row heights proportional to PDF layout
  • Bold, font size, and alignment preserved from source PDF

HOW IT WORKS (3 modes, auto-selected per page)
───────────────────────────────────────────────
  GRID  → PDF has drawn vertical lines (≥2)
          Column boundaries come from those lines
          → IRS forms, PA-3, forms with printed boxes

  TABLE → pdfplumber detects table structure (≥2 cols)
          Full table extraction with proper header row
          → NY ST-810, MA ST-9, consolidated schedules

  TEXT  → Fallback: cluster text by x-position
          Handles any freeform positioned-text PDF
          → MD Form 202, simple tax return pages

